To apply this stepwise method using SAS, assuming the doses are labeled 1; . . . ; k with dose 1 being the control against which other doses should be compared, one can execute the code
PROC GLM; CLASS dose; MODEL response = dose; LSMEANS dose/PDIFF=CONTROLU(’1’) ADJUST=T CL ALPHA=.05;

and then compares the individual (not simultaneous) lower confidence bounds to D in a stepwise fashion, as illustrated below. 3.2.4 Dose finding study example (continued)

